# Playwright End-to-End Testing

Playwright automates Chromium, Firefox, and WebKit with a single API. It eliminates flaky tests through auto-waiting, provides network interception for mocking, and includes visual comparison, codegen, and trace viewing out of the box.

## Quick Start

```bash
# Initialize a new Playwright project
npm init playwright@latest

# Or add to an existing project
npm install -D @playwright/test
npx playwright install --with-deps
```

This creates `playwright.config.ts`, a `tests/` directory with an example test, and installs browser binaries.

## First Test

```typescript
// tests/example.spec.ts
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test('homepage has title', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('https://example.com');
  await expect(page).toHaveTitle(/Example/);
});

test('login flow', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/login');
  await page.getByLabel('Email').fill('user@example.com');
  await page.getByLabel('Password').fill('secret');
  await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Sign in' }).click();
  await expect(page.getByText('Welcome')).toBeVisible();
});
```

```bash
# Run all tests
npx playwright test

# Run with UI mode (interactive)
npx playwright test --ui

# Run a specific file
npx playwright test tests/login.spec.ts

# Run in headed mode (see the browser)
npx playwright test --headed

# Run only tests matching a pattern
npx playwright test --grep "login"

# Run in a specific project/browser
npx playwright test --project=chromium

# Show HTML report
npx playwright show-report
```

## Configuration

```typescript
// playwright.config.ts
import { defineConfig, devices } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  testDir: './tests',
  fullyParallel: true,
  forbidOnly: !!process.env.CI,
  retries: process.env.CI ? 2 : 0,
  workers: process.env.CI ? 1 : undefined,
  reporter: process.env.CI ? 'blob' : 'html',
  use: {
    baseURL: 'http://localhost:3000',
    trace: 'on-first-retry',
    screenshot: 'only-on-failure',
    video: 'retain-on-failure',
  },
  projects: [
    { name: 'chromium', use: { ...devices['Desktop Chrome'] } },
    { name: 'firefox', use: { ...devices['Desktop Firefox'] } },
    { name: 'webkit', use: { ...devices['Desktop Safari'] } },
    { name: 'mobile-chrome', use: { ...devices['Pixel 5'] } },
    { name: 'mobile-safari', use: { ...devices['iPhone 13'] } },
  ],
  webServer: {
    command: 'npm run dev',
    url: 'http://localhost:3000',
    reuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI,
  },
});
```

Key config options:
- `fullyParallel` — run tests in parallel within files (not just across files)
- `forbidOnly` — fail in CI if `.only` is left in tests
- `retries` — retry failed tests (useful in CI)
- `workers` — number of parallel workers
- `trace` — `'on-first-retry'` captures traces only on first retry for debugging
- `webServer` — automatically start your dev server before tests
- `projects` — run the same tests across multiple browser/device configurations

## Writing Tests — Page Interactions

```typescript
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test('fill out form and submit', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/register');

  // Fill form fields
  await page.getByLabel('Full name').fill('Alice Johnson');
  await page.getByLabel('Email').fill('alice@example.com');
  await page.getByLabel('Password').fill('Str0ng!Pass');

  // Select from dropdown
  await page.getByLabel('Country').selectOption('US');

  // Check a checkbox
  await page.getByLabel('I agree to the terms').check();

  // Click submit
  await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Create account' }).click();

  // Assert success
  await expect(page.getByText('Account created')).toBeVisible();
  await expect(page).toHaveURL('/dashboard');
});
```

Common page actions:
- `page.goto(url)` — navigate to URL
- `page.click(selector)` — click an element
- `page.fill(selector, value)` — clear and type into an input
- `page.type(selector, value)` — type character by character
- `page.selectOption(selector, value)` — select dropdown option
- `page.check(selector)` / `page.uncheck(selector)` — checkbox
- `page.press(selector, key)` — press a key (e.g., `'Enter'`)
- `page.waitForURL(pattern)` — wait for navigation
- `page.waitForResponse(urlOrPredicate)` — wait for network response

## Locator Strategies

Playwright recommends user-facing locators that mirror how users find elements:

```typescript
// PREFERRED: role-based locators (most resilient)
page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Submit' });
page.getByRole('heading', { name: 'Dashboard' });
page.getByRole('link', { name: 'Settings' });
page.getByRole('textbox', { name: 'Search' });
page.getByRole('checkbox', { name: 'Remember me' });

// Text-based
page.getByText('Welcome back');
page.getByText('Welcome', { exact: false });

// Label-based (for form fields)
page.getByLabel('Email address');
page.getByLabel('Password');

// Placeholder-based
page.getByPlaceholder('Search...');

// Test ID (when no better semantic locator exists)
page.getByTestId('nav-menu');

// CSS and XPath (escape hatch — avoid when possible)
page.locator('.card-container >> .title');
page.locator('css=button.primary');
page.locator('xpath=//div[@data-id="main"]');

// Chaining and filtering
page.getByRole('listitem').filter({ hasText: 'Product A' });
page.getByRole('listitem').filter({ has: page.getByRole('button') });
page.locator('.card').nth(2);
page.locator('.card').first();
page.locator('.card').last();
```

Locator priority (most to least resilient):
1. `getByRole` — accessibility-based, survives refactors
2. `getByLabel` — form fields by associated label
3. `getByPlaceholder` — inputs by placeholder text
4. `getByText` — visible text content
5. `getByTestId` — data-testid attributes (explicit contract)
6. `locator('css')` — CSS selectors (fragile, avoid)

## Assertions

```typescript
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test('assertions demo', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/products');

  // Page-level assertions
  await expect(page).toHaveTitle('Products | My Store');
  await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\/products/);

  // Visibility
  await expect(page.getByText('Featured')).toBeVisible();
  await expect(page.getByText('Admin Panel')).toBeHidden();
  await expect(page.getByText('Admin Panel')).not.toBeVisible();

  // Text content
  await expect(page.getByRole('heading')).toHaveText('Products');
  await expect(page.getByRole('heading')).toContainText('Prod');

  // Count
  await expect(page.getByRole('listitem')).toHaveCount(5);

  // Form state
  await expect(page.getByLabel('Email')).toHaveValue('user@test.com');
  await expect(page.getByLabel('Email')).toBeEditable();
  await expect(page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Submit' })).toBeEnabled();
  await expect(page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Submit' })).toBeDisabled();

  // Checkbox / radio
  await expect(page.getByLabel('Newsletter')).toBeChecked();
  await expect(page.getByLabel('Newsletter')).not.toBeChecked();

  // CSS
  await expect(page.locator('.alert')).toHaveClass(/alert-danger/);
  await expect(page.locator('.header')).toHaveCSS('color', 'rgb(0, 0, 0)');

  // Attributes
  await expect(page.getByRole('link')).toHaveAttribute('href', '/home');

  // Soft assertions (continue test on failure, report at end)
  await expect.soft(page.getByText('Beta')).toBeVisible();
});
```

All `expect(locator)` assertions auto-wait and auto-retry until the condition is met or the timeout expires. Default timeout is 5 seconds, configurable per-assertion or globally.

## Network Mocking

```typescript
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test('mock API response', async ({ page }) => {
  // Intercept API calls and return mock data
  await page.route('**/api/products', async (route) => {
    await route.fulfill({
      status: 200,
      contentType: 'application/json',
      body: JSON.stringify([
        { id: 1, name: 'Widget', price: 9.99 },
        { id: 2, name: 'Gadget', price: 19.99 },
      ]),
    });
  });

  await page.goto('/products');
  await expect(page.getByText('Widget')).toBeVisible();
  await expect(page.getByText('Gadget')).toBeVisible();
});

test('mock error response', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.route('**/api/products', async (route) => {
    await route.fulfill({ status: 500, body: 'Internal Server Error' });
  });

  await page.goto('/products');
  await expect(page.getByText('Failed to load')).toBeVisible();
});

test('modify real response', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.route('**/api/user', async (route) => {
    const response = await route.fetch();
    const json = await response.json();
    json.name = 'Test User';
    await route.fulfill({ response, body: JSON.stringify(json) });
  });

  await page.goto('/profile');
  await expect(page.getByText('Test User')).toBeVisible();
});

test('abort requests', async ({ page }) => {
  // Block analytics and tracking
  await page.route('**/*analytics*', (route) => route.abort());
  await page.route('**/ads/**', (route) => route.abort());
  await page.goto('/home');
});

test('wait for specific response', async ({ page }) => {
  const responsePromise = page.waitForResponse('**/api/data');
  await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Load' }).click();
  const response = await responsePromise;
  expect(response.status()).toBe(200);
});
```

## Visual Testing — Screenshots and Snapshots

```typescript
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test('visual comparison', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/dashboard');

  // Full page screenshot comparison
  await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot('dashboard.png');

  // Element screenshot comparison
  await expect(page.locator('.chart')).toHaveScreenshot('chart.png');

  // With options
  await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot('dashboard-full.png', {
    fullPage: true,
    maxDiffPixelRatio: 0.05,  // allow 5% pixel difference
  });

  // Mask dynamic content
  await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot('dashboard-stable.png', {
    mask: [page.locator('.timestamp'), page.locator('.avatar')],
  });
});

test('snapshot comparison (text)', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/api/health');
  const body = await page.textContent('body');
  expect(body).toMatchSnapshot('health-response.txt');
});
```

First run creates reference screenshots in a `*-snapshots/` directory. Subsequent runs compare against the reference. Update snapshots with `npx playwright test --update-snapshots`.

## Authentication — Reusing Login State

```typescript
// auth.setup.ts — runs once, saves login state
import { test as setup, expect } from '@playwright/test';

const authFile = 'playwright/.auth/user.json';

setup('authenticate', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/login');
  await page.getByLabel('Email').fill('user@example.com');
  await page.getByLabel('Password').fill('password');
  await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Sign in' }).click();
  await page.waitForURL('/dashboard');
  await page.context().storageState({ path: authFile });
});
```

```typescript
// playwright.config.ts — configure auth setup and reuse
import { defineConfig } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  projects: [
    { name: 'setup', testMatch: /.*\.setup\.ts/ },
    {
      name: 'chromium',
      dependencies: ['setup'],
      use: {
        storageState: 'playwright/.auth/user.json',
      },
    },
  ],
});
```

This runs the auth setup once, saves cookies and localStorage to a JSON file, and reuses that state for all subsequent tests. Tests run already authenticated — no repeated login flows.

## Custom Fixtures

```typescript
import { test as base, expect } from '@playwright/test';

// Define custom fixture types
type Fixtures = {
  todoPage: TodoPage;
  loggedInPage: Page;
};

class TodoPage {
  constructor(private page: Page) {}

  async addTodo(text: string) {
    await this.page.getByPlaceholder('What needs to be done?').fill(text);
    await this.page.getByPlaceholder('What needs to be done?').press('Enter');
  }

  async getTodoCount() {
    return await this.page.getByTestId('todo-item').count();
  }
}

// Extend base test with custom fixtures
const test = base.extend<Fixtures>({
  todoPage: async ({ page }, use) => {
    await page.goto('/todos');
    await use(new TodoPage(page));
  },
});

test('add a todo', async ({ todoPage }) => {
  await todoPage.addTodo('Buy groceries');
  expect(await todoPage.getTodoCount()).toBe(1);
});
```

## Codegen — Recording Tests

```bash
# Open codegen and record actions as test code
npx playwright codegen https://example.com

# Record with specific viewport
npx playwright codegen --viewport-size=1280,720 https://example.com

# Record for a specific device
npx playwright codegen --device="iPhone 13" https://example.com

# Save recorded test to a file
npx playwright codegen --output=tests/recorded.spec.ts https://example.com
```

Codegen opens a browser and an inspector window. Every click, fill, and navigation is recorded as Playwright test code in real time. Copy the generated code into your test files and refine.

## Trace Viewer — Debugging Failures

Enable traces in config:

```typescript
// playwright.config.ts
use: {
  trace: 'on-first-retry',  // capture trace on first retry of a failed test
}
```

Trace options: `'off'`, `'on'`, `'retain-on-failure'`, `'on-first-retry'`, `'on-all-retries'`.

```bash
# View traces from test results
npx playwright show-trace test-results/example-test/trace.zip

# Or open trace viewer and drag-drop a trace file
npx playwright show-trace
```

The trace viewer shows a timeline of every action, a DOM snapshot at each step, network requests, console logs, and the test source code. It is the primary tool for diagnosing why a test failed.

## Parallel Execution

```typescript
// playwright.config.ts
export default defineConfig({
  fullyParallel: true,          // parallelize within files
  workers: process.env.CI ? 1 : undefined,  // auto-detect locally, single in CI
});
```

```typescript
// Force serial execution for tests that share state
test.describe.serial('checkout flow', () => {
  test('add to cart', async ({ page }) => { /* ... */ });
  test('enter shipping', async ({ page }) => { /* ... */ });
  test('complete payment', async ({ page }) => { /* ... */ });
});

// Explicit parallel block
test.describe.parallel('independent tests', () => {
  test('test A', async ({ page }) => { /* ... */ });
  test('test B', async ({ page }) => { /* ... */ });
});
```

Each test gets its own browser context (cookies, localStorage) by default. Tests are isolated without extra effort.

## CI Setup

```yaml
# .github/workflows/playwright.yml
name: Playwright Tests
on: [push, pull_request]
jobs:
  test:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: 20
      - run: npm ci
      - run: npx playwright install --with-deps
      - run: npx playwright test
      - uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
        if: ${{ !cancelled() }}
        with:
          name: playwright-report
          path: playwright-report/
          retention-days: 30
```

CI best practices:
- Always run `npx playwright install --with-deps` (installs browser binaries and OS dependencies)
- Set `workers: 1` in CI config for deterministic results on resource-constrained runners
- Set `retries: 2` in CI for resilience against transient failures
- Upload the HTML report as an artifact for debugging
- Use `forbidOnly: !!process.env.CI` to prevent `.only` from sneaking into CI

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|----------|
| `CI` | Set automatically in CI — Playwright detects it for config switches |
| `PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH` | Custom directory for browser binaries (useful for caching) |
| `PWDEBUG` | Set to `1` to enable step-by-step debugging with inspector |
| `PLAYWRIGHT_HTML_OPEN` | Set to `never` in CI to suppress opening report in browser |
| `PLAYWRIGHT_TEST_BASE_URL` | Override `baseURL` from config without editing the file |
| `PLAYWRIGHT_SKIP_BROWSER_DOWNLOAD` | Set to `1` to skip browser download during npm install |

## Project Layout

```
project/
  playwright.config.ts
  tests/
    example.spec.ts
    auth.setup.ts
    login.spec.ts
    dashboard.spec.ts
  playwright/
    .auth/
      user.json           # stored authentication state
  test-results/           # test artifacts (traces, screenshots)
  playwright-report/      # HTML report output
  tests-examples/         # example tests from init (deletable)
```
